  <title>
    <phrase>Remove all guides</phrase>
    
    
    
    
    
    
  </title>

  <indexterm significance="normal">
    <primary>Guides</primary>
    <secondary>Remove</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  
  
  
  
  
  

  <para><!--TODO it:-->
    The <guilabel moreinfo="none">Remove all Guides</guilabel> command removes all guides
    from the image. Clicking-and-dragging one or two guides onto a ruler
    is a quicker way to remove them. This command is interesting if you have
    positioned several guides.
  </para>
  
  
  
  
  
  

  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activate the Command</phrase>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
    </title>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access this command from the image menubar through
          <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
            <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>I</accel>mage</guimenu>
            <guisubmenu moreinfo="none"><accel>G</accel>uides</guisubmenu>
            <guimenuitem moreinfo="none"><accel>R</accel>emove all guides</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>.
        </para>
        
        
        
        
        
        
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
